+# Multi-Currency Wallet System Implementation Plan
+
+## Context
+
+PiggyMetrics lets each income/expense Item carry its own Currency, and the statistics-service normalizes everything to USD for its datapoints, but the account-service has no concept of a wallet. There is no way for a user to see a total balance across all currencies converted into a preferred display currency. This plan adds a multi-currency wallet system to the account-service: per-currency balances, monthly normalization, currency conversion via the statistics-service, REST endpoints, and daily snapshots.
+
+---
+
+## Part 1: Statistics-Service (expose exchange rates)
+
+### 1.1 Add `/rates` endpoint to StatisticsController
+**Modify:** `statistics-service/src/main/java/.../statistics/controller/StatisticsController.java`
+- Inject `ExchangeRatesService` (alongside existing `StatisticsService`)
+- Add `GET /rates` method with `@PreAuthorize("#oauth2.hasScope('server')")` returning `Map<Currency, BigDecimal>` from `exchangeRatesService.getCurrentRates()`
+
+### 1.2 Add test for `/rates` endpoint
+**Modify:** `statistics-service/src/test/java/.../statistics/controller/StatisticsControllerTest.java`
+- Add `@Mock ExchangeRatesService exchangeRatesService`
+- Add `shouldGetCurrentRates()` test case
+
+---
+
+## Part 2: Account-Service Domain Model
+
+### 2.1 Add month ratios to TimePeriod enum
+**Modify:** `account-service/src/main/java/.../account/domain/TimePeriod.java`
+
+Currently a plain enum. Add a `monthRatio` field so `monthlyAmount = amount * period.getMonthRatio()`:
+- `YEAR(1.0/12.0)`, `QUARTER(1.0/3.0)`, `MONTH(1.0)`, `DAY(30.4368)`, `HOUR(30.4368*24.0)`
+
+### 2.2 Create Wallet domain class
+**New:** `account-service/src/main/java/.../account/domain/Wallet.java`
+
+Fields: `Map<Currency,BigDecimal> balances`, `Map<Currency,BigDecimal> convertedBalances`, `BigDecimal totalBalance`, `BigDecimal totalMonthlyIncome`, `BigDecimal totalMonthlyExpenses`, `BigDecimal netSavingsRatePercent`, `Currency baseCurrency`, `Date lastUpdated`
+
+### 2.3 Create WalletSnapshot + WalletSnapshotId
+**New:** `account-service/src/main/java/.../account/domain/WalletSnapshot.java` - `@Document(collection="wallet_snapshots")` with `@Id WalletSnapshotId id` and `Wallet wallet`
+
+**New:** `account-service/src/main/java/.../account/domain/WalletSnapshotId.java` - compound key with `String account` + `Date date` (mirrors DataPointId pattern from statistics-service)
+
+### 2.4 Add Wallet field to Account
+**Modify:** `account-service/src/main/java/.../account/domain/Account.java`
+- Add `private Wallet wallet` with getter/setter. Existing documents without wallet will deserialize to `null` (no backward compat issue).
+
+---
+
+## Part 3: Account-Service Infrastructure
+
+### 3.1 Create ExchangeRatesClient Feign interface
+**New:** `account-service/src/main/java/.../account/client/ExchangeRatesClient.java`
+- `@FeignClient(name="statistics-service", contextId="exchangeRatesClient", fallback=ExchangeRatesClientFallback.class)`
+- `GET /rates` returning `Map<Currency, BigDecimal>`
+
+### 3.2 Create ExchangeRatesClientFallback
+**New:** `account-service/src/main/java/.../account/client/ExchangeRatesClientFallback.java`
+- Returns hardcoded approximate rates: `USD=1, EUR=0.9, RUB=75.0`
+- Logs warning (follows StatisticsServiceClientFallback pattern)
+
+### 3.3 Create MongoDB converters for WalletSnapshotId
+**New:** `account-service/src/main/java/.../account/repository/converter/WalletSnapshotIdReaderConverter.java`
+**New:** `account-service/src/main/java/.../account/repository/converter/WalletSnapshotIdWriterConverter.java`
+- Follows DataPointId converter pattern from statistics-service
+
+### 3.4 Register converters in AccountApplication
+**Modify:** `account-service/src/main/java/.../account/AccountApplication.java`
+- Add `CustomConversionsConfig` inner class with `CustomConversions` bean (same pattern as StatisticsApplication)
+
+### 3.5 Create WalletSnapshotRepository
+**New:** `account-service/src/main/java/.../account/repository/WalletSnapshotRepository.java`
+- `CrudRepository<WalletSnapshot, WalletSnapshotId>`
+- `findByIdAccount(String account)`
+- `findByIdAccountAndIdDateBetween(String account, Date from, Date to)`
+
+---
+
+## Part 4: Account-Service Core Logic
+
+### 4.1 Create WalletService interface
+**New:** `account-service/src/main/java/.../account/service/WalletService.java`
+- `Wallet getWallet(String accountName)`
+- `Wallet recalculate(String accountName)`
+- `Wallet changeBaseCurrency(String accountName, Currency currency)`
+- `List<WalletSnapshot> getHistory(String accountName, Date from, Date to)`
+
+### 4.2 Create WalletServiceImpl
+**New:** `account-service/src/main/java/.../account/service/WalletServiceImpl.java`
+
+Core `buildWallet(Account, Currency baseCurrency)` method:
+1. Fetch rates from `exchangeRatesClient.getRates()`
+2. Normalize all income items to monthly amounts: `amount * period.getMonthRatio()`
+3. Normalize all expense items to monthly amounts
+4. Compute per-currency native balances (income - expense per currency)
+5. Convert each per-currency balance to base display currency
+6. Sum total monthly income/expenses in base currency
+7. Add Saving amount (converted to base currency) to get total balance: `totalBalance = (totalIncome - totalExpenses) + savingInBase`
+8. Compute savings rate: `(income - expenses) / income * 100`
+
+`recalculate()` - loads account, calls buildWallet, saves wallet on account, saves daily snapshot
+`changeBaseCurrency()` - loads account, calls buildWallet with new currency, saves
+`saveSnapshot()` - uses compound ID (account + start-of-day) so same-day saves upsert
+
+Dependencies: `AccountRepository`, `WalletSnapshotRepository`, `ExchangeRatesClient` (no circular dependency with AccountService)
+
+### 4.3 Wire into AccountServiceImpl.saveChanges()
+**Modify:** `account-service/src/main/java/.../account/service/AccountServiceImpl.java`
+- Inject `WalletService`
+- After existing save + statisticsClient call, add `walletService.recalculate(name)` wrapped in try-catch (wallet failure must not break account save)
+
+---
+
+## Part 5: REST Endpoints
+
+### 5.1 Create WalletController
+**New:** `account-service/src/main/java/.../account/controller/WalletController.java`
+- `GET /current/wallet` - get current wallet
+- `POST /current/wallet/refresh` - force recalculate
+- `PUT /current/wallet/currency` - change base currency (body: Currency enum value)
+- `GET /current/wallet/history?from=X&to=Y` - wallet snapshots by date range
+
+All use `Principal` for auth (consistent with AccountController). All fall under existing `.anyRequest().authenticated()` security config.
+
+---
+
+## Part 6: Tests
+
+### 6.1 WalletServiceTest
+**New:** `account-service/src/test/java/.../account/service/WalletServiceTest.java`
+- Tests: single currency, multi-currency, time period normalization, saving inclusion, savings rate, base currency change, null incomes/expenses, account not found, snapshot creation
+
+### 6.2 WalletControllerTest
+**New:** `account-service/src/test/java/.../account/controller/WalletControllerTest.java`
+- Tests: GET wallet, POST refresh, PUT currency, GET history
+
+### 6.3 ExchangeRatesClientFallbackTest
+**New:** `account-service/src/test/java/.../account/client/ExchangeRatesClientFallbackTest.java`
+
+### 6.4 Update existing AccountServiceTest
+**Modify:** `account-service/src/test/java/.../account/service/AccountServiceTest.java`
+- Add `@Mock WalletService walletService` so saveChanges test works with new injection
+
+### 6.5 Update existing StatisticsControllerTest
+**Modify:** `statistics-service/src/test/java/.../statistics/controller/StatisticsControllerTest.java`
+- Add `@Mock ExchangeRatesService` + test for `/rates`
+
+---
+
+## File Summary
+
+**New files (11):**
+- `account-service/.../client/ExchangeRatesClient.java`
+- `account-service/.../client/ExchangeRatesClientFallback.java`
+- `account-service/.../domain/Wallet.java`
+- `account-service/.../domain/WalletSnapshot.java`
+- `account-service/.../domain/WalletSnapshotId.java`
+- `account-service/.../repository/WalletSnapshotRepository.java`
+- `account-service/.../repository/converter/WalletSnapshotIdReaderConverter.java`
+- `account-service/.../repository/converter/WalletSnapshotIdWriterConverter.java`
+- `account-service/.../service/WalletService.java`
+- `account-service/.../service/WalletServiceImpl.java`
+- `account-service/.../controller/WalletController.java`
+
+**New test files (3):**
+- `account-service/.../service/WalletServiceTest.java`
+- `account-service/.../controller/WalletControllerTest.java`
+- `account-service/.../client/ExchangeRatesClientFallbackTest.java`
+
+**Modified files (7):**
+- `statistics-service/.../controller/StatisticsController.java` (add `/rates` endpoint)
+- `statistics-service/.../controller/StatisticsControllerTest.java` (add rates test)
+- `account-service/.../domain/TimePeriod.java` (add month ratios)
+- `account-service/.../domain/Account.java` (add wallet field)
+- `account-service/.../service/AccountServiceImpl.java` (trigger wallet recalculation)
+- `account-service/.../AccountApplication.java` (register MongoDB converters)
+- `account-service/.../service/AccountServiceTest.java` (add WalletService mock)
+
+---
+
+## Verification
+
+1. `mvn test -pl statistics-service` - all existing + new rates endpoint test pass
+2. `mvn test -pl account-service` - all existing + new wallet tests pass
+3. `mvn package` for both services - clean build
+4. Existing GET/PUT endpoints return same structure (wallet is additive `null` field on old accounts)
